# About exa
# exa is a modern replacement for ls. 
# It uses colours for information by default, helping you distinguish between many types of files, 
# such as whether you are the owner, or in the owning group. 
# It also has extra features not present in the original ls, such as viewing the Git status for a directory, 
# or recursing into directories with a tree view. exa is written in Rust, 
# so itâ€™s small, fast, and portable.
#
# References:
#

# Display 1 entry per line
exa -l

# Show extended attributes
exa -l

# Recurse into directories
exa -R

# Show a tree
exa -T

# Reverse the sort order
exa -r
